<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
<p class="muted">Last updated: July 2026</p>

<p>
  "Web Scraping by K.AI Labs" (the "Extension") and its companion web app ("K.AI Labs",
  "we") help you run SEO checks on web pages using an AI model of your choice. This page
  explains what data we collect, how it's used, and how it's protected.
</p>

<h2>What we collect</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Account info</strong>: the email and password you sign up with. Passwords are
    hashed (bcrypt) and never stored in plain text.</li>
  <li><strong>Your AI API key</strong>: you bring your own key (OpenAI, Anthropic, or Google AI).
    It is encrypted at rest (AES-256-GCM) before being stored and is only decrypted in memory,
    server-side, to make the AI request you triggered. We never display it back to you in full,
    and never share it with anyone other than the provider you chose, to fulfill your request.</li>
  <li><strong>Page data you choose to analyze</strong>: when you click "Analyze this page" in the
    Extension, on-page content (title, meta tags, headings, structured data, links, performance
    timing) from the currently open tab is read, sent to your chosen AI provider to plan the
    check, and the resulting findings are sent to our backend to display results and save your
    history. This only happens when you explicitly trigger it — the Extension does not scan pages
    in the background.</li>
  <li><strong>Check history</strong>: the URL, check type, and results of each analysis you run,
    tied to your account, so you can review past checks on your dashboard.</li>
</ul>

<h2>What we don't do</h2>
<ul>
  <li>We don't sell or share your data with advertisers or data brokers.</li>
  <li>We don't read page content unless you explicitly run a check on that page.</li>
  <li>We don't store your AI API key in plain text, and we don't use it for anything other than
    the request you made.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Why the Extension asks for broad permissions</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Read/change data on all websites</strong>: needed so you can run an SEO check on
    any page you're viewing, not just a fixed list of sites.</li>
  <li><strong>Storage</strong>: used locally in your browser to keep you signed in.</li>
  <li><strong>Scripting</strong>: used to run the on-page scan when you click "Analyze", and only
    then.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Your controls</h2>
<p>
  You can remove a stored AI API key at any time from your dashboard. You can log out of the
  Extension at any time, which deletes the locally stored session token. To delete your account
  and all associated data, contact us using the details below.
</p>

<h2>Contact</h2>
